    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-thigh-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and chop roughly (or grate)</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>garlic </strong>roughly</p><p>Peel and dice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s] </strong>finely</p><p>Roll your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-thigh-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Split open your <strong>cardamom pods</strong>, removing the black inner seeds</p><p>Grind them slightly in a pestle and mortar, and heat a dry pan over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cardamom seeds </strong>to the pan with your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-thigh-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with<strong> </strong>a squeeze of<strong> lime juice</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong>,<strong> ground almonds</strong> and your <strong>honey </strong>and cook for 1-2 min</p><p>Transfer the mixture to a <strong>food processor</strong> (reserve the pan for later!) and blitz until smooth - this is your <strong>curry paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-thigh-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>chicken </strong>into strips</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken strips</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until until beginning to brown</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-thigh-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>curry paste</strong> to the pan with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [340ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and cook on a medium-low heat for 10 min, then remove the lid and reduce for 5 min further until thickened to a good consistency or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>turmeric chicken curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-thigh-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>trimmed green beans</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/turmeric-chicken-thigh-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>turmeric chicken curry</strong> over the <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> and <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
